How to compile the project:
make

Example of how to run the project:
./oss -n 3 -s 2 -t 4 -i 0.6

Notes:
- Project implements oss/worker for the simulated clock assignment (project 2).
- oss maintains a simulated system clock in shared memory (seconds, nanoseconds).
- worker attaches to shared memory to read the clock and determines its termination time based on input.
- oss manages a process table, launches workers with a minimum interval, and prints periodic system state.
- oss uses -t as a simulated time limit for launching new workers.
- oss terminates after all workers complete and handles a real-time 60s shutdown with cleanup.
- No sleep/usleep is used in worker timing loops (simulated time only).

